    "state_reason": "completed",
    "title": "Wallet file should not be reused across chains",
    "body": "Now that it is possible to specify a full path for the wallet (or a walletdir), the same wallet file is happily reused even when switching chains.\r\n\r\nImo that use case has no purpose, since all transactions on one chain are invalid on the other. It might be better to return an `InitError` in that case than writing useless data to a wallet file of a different chain.",
